<PageLayout title="About" description="Learn about the Los Angeles Bicycle Advisory Committee, its mission, and history since 1975.">
  <p class="text-lg text-text-muted mb-6">
    The Los Angeles Bicycle Advisory Committee (LABAC) has been advising the City of Los Angeles on bicycle transportation since 1975.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary mt-8 mb-3">Our Mission</h2>
  <p class="text-text-muted mb-4">
    LABAC advises the Mayor, City Council, and City departments on policies, programs, and projects that affect bicycle transportation in the City of Los Angeles.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary mt-8 mb-3">History</h2>
  <p class="text-text-muted mb-4">
    Established in 1975, LABAC is one of the oldest bicycle advisory committees in the United States. The committee has played a key role in shaping Los Angeles's bicycle infrastructure and policy.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary mt-8 mb-3">What We Do</h2>
  <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-text-muted space-y-2">
    <li>Review and comment on bicycle-related projects and plans</li>
    <li>Advise on the City's Bicycle Plan and Mobility Plan</li>
    <li>Provide a public forum for bicycle transportation issues</li>
    <li>Collaborate with LADOT, Metro, and other agencies</li>
  </ul>
</PageLayout>
